{"id":65280,"date":"2017-02-13T06:12:09","date_gmt":"2017-02-13T14:12:09","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/?p=65280"},"modified":"2017-02-13T06:14:34","modified_gmt":"2017-02-13T14:14:34","slug":"edx-amazon-moocs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/edx-amazon-moocs\/","title":{"rendered":"You Can Now Purchase edX Courses on Amazon.com"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Finance-for-Everyone-MOOC-Amazon.jpg\" alt=\"edX Finance for Everyone MOOC - Amazon\" width=\"100%\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Finance-for-Everyone-MOOC-Amazon.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Finance-for-Everyone-MOOC-Amazon-300x166.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Finance-for-Everyone-MOOC-Amazon-768x426.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Finance-for-Everyone-MOOC-Amazon-1024x568.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/provider\/edx\">EdX<\/a>, the second largest MOOC provider in the world,\u00a0has made a few of its courses available on Amazon, the largest internet-based retailer in the world.<\/p>\n<p>At the time of writing this article, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/edX\/b\/ref=kedu_bl_s_web_10211452011?ie=UTF8&amp;node=10211452011&amp;field-lbr_brands_browse-bin=edX\" target=\"_blank\">thirteen courses<\/a> have been listed on Amazon.com by edX. The prices range from $49 to $499. The courses are a mixture: some are\u00a0taught by universities (such as the University of Michigan and Tsinghua University), and\u00a0others are taught by companies (like Microsoft and Linux Foundation).<\/p>\n<p>Once you purchase a course on Amazon, you will receive a code that can be redeemed on edX.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65285\" src=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/How-to-Access-Your-Courses-on-Amazon.png\" alt=\"How to Access Your Courses on Amazon\" width=\"100%\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/How-to-Access-Your-Courses-on-Amazon.png 2796w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/How-to-Access-Your-Courses-on-Amazon-300x79.png 300w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/How-to-Access-Your-Courses-on-Amazon-768x202.png 768w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/How-to-Access-Your-Courses-on-Amazon-1024x270.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2796px) 100vw, 2796px\" \/><\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"cc-blockquote cc-blockquote-right cc-blockquote-image\"><p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-65286\" src=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Amazon-What-You-Get.png\" alt=\"edX Amazon What You Get\" width=\"276\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Amazon-What-You-Get.png 902w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Amazon-What-You-Get-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Amazon-What-You-Get-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/edX-Amazon-What-You-Get-768x766.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 276px) 100vw, 276px\" \/><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>A majority of the courses edX have listed on Amazon.com are normally free; you can access the content on edX for free. What you are actually paying for on Amazon is a verified certificate. But the descriptions on Amazon fail to communicate that the courses are, in fact, free to take.<\/p>\n<p>Since only a few courses are listed, it seems like edX is only testing the waters so far. But the benefits for edX\u00a0are pretty clear: it gets to distribute its courses to hundreds of millions of Amazon users, and so potentially increase its revenue.<\/p>\n<p>From Amazon&#8217;s point of view, it seems to be slowly trying to build a storefront for online education, at least with its US site. Last year it announced a <a href=\"http:\/\/www.usatoday.com\/story\/tech\/columnist\/2016\/08\/30\/cutting-cord-great-courses-amazon-prime-streaming\/89001148\/\">partnership<\/a> with The Great Courses. With an add-on subscription to Amazon Prime, users can get access to\u00a0The Great Courses&#8217; &#8220;Signature Collection&#8221; via Amazon.<\/p>\n<p>Currently, Amazon has over 7,000 &#8220;educational courses&#8221; that can be purchased on its site. You can find them <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/STRING-courseware_url_desc\/b\/ref=topnav_storetab_crss_sbnv_rt?ie=UTF8&amp;node=14297978011\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Below is a complete <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/edX\/b\/ref=kedu_bl_s_web_10211452011?ie=UTF8&amp;node=10211452011&amp;field-lbr_brands_browse-bin=edX\">list<\/a> of edX courses that can be purchased on Amazon, along with their prices (where known):<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Introduction to R, from Microsoft \u2014\u00a0$49<\/li>\n<li>Chinese Language: Learn Basic Mandarin \u2014 $49<\/li>\n<li>Learn Spanish: Basic Spanish for English Speakers, from\u00a0Universitat Politecnica de Valencia \u2014 $49<\/li>\n<li>Programming with C#, from Microsoft \u2014 $90<\/li>\n<li>Conversational English Skills, from Tsinghua University \u2014 $49<\/li>\n<li>Essentials of Linux Systems Administration, from Linux Foundation \u2014 $499<\/li>\n<li>Introduction to Linux, from Linux Foundation \u2014 $99.99<\/li>\n<li>Finance for Everyone: Smart Tools for Decision-Making, from University of Michigan \u2014 $49<\/li>\n<li>IELTS Academic Test Preparation, from University of Queensland \u2014 $99<\/li>\n<li>AP Macroeconomics Challenging Concepts, from\u00a0Davidson College \u2014 $49<\/li>\n<li>World of Wine: From Grape to Glass, from\u00a0University of Adelaide \u2014 currently\u00a0unavailable<\/li>\n<li>The Road to Selective College Admissions, from\u00a0St. Margaret\u2019s Episcopal School \u2014 currently unavailable<\/li>\n<li>Introduction to Programming with Java, Part 1: Starting to Code in Java \u2014 currently unavailable<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<hr \/>\n<p><strong>Related:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/edx-2016-review\/\">edX\u2019s 2016: Year in Review<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/oms-analytics\/\">Georgia Tech and edX Announce an Online Master of Science in Analytics Degree<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/anant-agarwal-padma-shri\/\">Edx Crosses 10 Million Learners, CEO Chosen for an Award by the Indian Government\u00a0<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>EdX testing a potential new revenue source by making a few of its courses available on Amazon.com; Amazon strengthens its move into online learning.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":65281,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[103],"tags":[51],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO Premium plugin v18.3 (Yoast SEO v18.5.1) - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>You Can Now Purchase edX Courses on Amazon.com \u2014 Class Central<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"EdX testing a potential new revenue source by making a few of its courses available on Amazon.com; Amazon strengthens its move into online learning.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/re